To play Pyramid, you need a full deck of playing cards.
Cards are randomly drawn and placed in a pyramid pattern 1-2-3-4-5-6-7 with the remaining cards in a deck below
The user must select two cards that add up to 13. Cards are values 1-13 A-K.

GOALS:
- working board
- indicator of what cards are currently selected
- player can choose if they want deck flipped in 3s or 1s.
- working hints

Stretch Goals:
- Easy, Med, Hard modes
- fun animations



Code layout:
Main:
- Initializer()